<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>SECR Telecom Position Dashboard Summary</title>
  <style>
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Segoe+UI:wght@400;600;700;800&display=swap');
    
    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;
      color: #1e293b;
      background-color: #ffffff;
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin: 40px;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    
    header {
      border-bottom: 3px solid #2563eb;
      padding-bottom: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }
    
    .title-area h1 {
      font-size: 24px;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: #0f172a;
      margin: 0 0 6px 0;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }
    
    .title-area p {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 13px;
      color: #64748b;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    
    h2 {
      font-size: 16px;
      font-weight: 750;
      color: #1e293b;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
      padding-bottom: 6px;
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.3px;
    }
    
    h3 {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #334155;
      margin-top: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    
    p {
      margin-top: 0;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      color: #334155;
    }
    
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin-bottom: 25px;
      margin-top: 10px;
    }
    
    th, td {
      padding: 10px 12px;
      text-align: left;
      border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    }
    
    th {
      background-color: #f8fafc;
      color: #0f172a;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 12px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }
    
    td {
      font-size: 13px;
      color: #334155;
    }
    
    tr:nth-child(even) td {
      background-color: #fcfdfe;
    }
    
    ul, ol {
      margin-top: 0;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      padding-left: 20px;
    }
    
    li {
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      color: #334155;
    }
    
    code {
      font-family: Consolas, Monaco, monospace;
      background-color: #f1f5f9;
      color: #0f172a;
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    
    .footer {
      margin-top: 50px;
      border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
      padding-top: 15px;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 11px;
      color: #94a3b8;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <div class="title-area">
      <h1>SECR Telecom Position Dashboard</h1>
      <p>System Architecture, Data Flows, and Refactored Forms Summary</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>
      The <strong>South East Central Railway (SECR) Divisional Telecom Position Dashboard</strong> is a Next.js web application designed for telecom engineers to record, monitor, and update the status of telecom circuits, cable infrastructure, and surveillance systems across three railway divisions: <strong>Bilaspur</strong>, <strong>Raipur</strong>, and <strong>Nagpur</strong>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Technology Stack</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Core System</strong>: Next.js 16 (React 19, Turbopack) & TypeScript</li>
      <li><strong>Styling & Design System</strong>: Vanilla CSS for maximum performance, responsiveness, and premium dark/glassmorphic aesthetics</li>
      <li><strong>State Management</strong>: React Hooks (<code>useState</code>, <code>useMemo</code>, <code>useRef</code>, <code>useEffect</code>) for real-time calculations and zero-latency view updates</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Application Flow & User Operations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Division Filter Context</strong>: Globally filters major sections, sections, and stations for consistent reporting.</li>
      <li><strong>Categorized Circuit Workspace Selection</strong>: Selecting a circuit dynamically displays its dedicated entry form in the viewport.</li>
      <li><strong>Real-time failure duration calculation</strong>: Calculations are performed on-the-fly using <code>useMemo</code>, outputting formatted durations automatically.</li>
      <li><strong>"All OK" Workflow Accelerator</strong>: Allows one-click logging of 100% healthy status across all elements and automatically advances to the next circuit.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Summary of Refactored Dedicated Forms</h2>
    <p>
      Each circuit has been upgraded from generic layouts to customized forms designed for quick data entry and aligned side-by-side:
    </p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Category</th>
          <th>Circuit Name</th>
          <th>Custom Features & Forms Layout</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Network & Internet</strong></td>
          <td><strong>PRS/UTS</strong></td>
          <td>Consolidated UTS/PRS. Fields: System Type, Major Section/Section, Station, Nature of Fault (Equipment/Link), Failure & Rectification Times, auto-calculated Duration, Reason, and Remarks.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Network & Internet</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Railnet / Internet</strong></td>
          <td>Removed redundant searchable location dropdown. Provides dedicated Divisional Maintenance and HQ Maintenance tab layouts.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Network & Internet</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Wi-Fi</strong></td>
          <td>Dedicated form tracking: Location of faulty AP, Failure & Rectification Times, auto-calculated Duration, Reason of Failure, and Remarks.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>CCTV</strong></td>
          <td><strong>CCTV Monitoring</strong></td>
          <td>Dedicated fields: Major Section/Section, Total CCTV/Not working CCTV, Live Feed To War Room Failed status, Failure & Rectification Times, Duration, Reason, and Remarks.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>CCTV</strong></td>
          <td><strong>CCTV Maintenance</strong></td>
          <td>Mirror layout of CCTV Monitoring, dedicated to hardware servicing and disk checks.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Cable Infrastructure</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Cable Cut (OFC & Quad)</strong></td>
          <td>Laid out in clean 2-column grid: Major Section/Section, Station/Location, Km.No., Cable Type, Cable Cut by Whom, Failure & Rectification Times, Duration, Reason, and Remarks.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Cable Infrastructure</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Temporary Joints</strong></td>
          <td>Excludes Station/Location field. Tracks Section/Yard, Km.No., cable type, temporary joints count, rectified joints, TDC, Action Plan, and auto-calculates Balance Joints.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Cable Infrastructure</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Low Insulation</strong></td>
          <td>Excludes yard/section text inputs. Pairs Major Section, Section, Station/Location, Km.No., Cable Type, Total Insulation Faults, Rectified Date & Time, Balance Insulation Faults, Action Plan/TDC, and Remarks.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Display System</strong></td>
          <td><strong>CGDM</strong></td>
          <td>Tracks platform number (PF No.), number of faulty guidance boards, Failure Time, Rectification Time, Duration, Reason, and Remarks.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Display System</strong></td>
          <td><strong>TIB</strong></td>
          <td>Tracks location of faulty TIB, number of faulty boards, Failure Time, Rectification Time, Duration, Reason, and Remarks.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Testing & Maintenance</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Walkie-Talkie Repairing</strong></td>
          <td>Excludes icmsEntryNo requirement. Tracks Defective/Repaired set counts, Sets Condemned, target condemnation dates, repair status, action taken, and repair faults.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5. Project File Map</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Main Component Logic</strong>: <code>src/app/page.tsx</code></li>
      <li><strong>Global CSS Styling</strong>: <code>src/app/globals.css</code></li>
      <li><strong>Tasks Registry</strong>: <code>task.md</code></li>
      <li><strong>Walkthrough History</strong>: <code>walkthrough.md</code></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <div class="footer">
    South East Central Railway © 2026 - Confidential Internal Telecom Document
  </div>

</body>
</html>
